# assign-slot.word, a being binds one of its connections to a slot on its OWN being
# (llm-assigner/ops.js assign-slot DO op). PURE-COMPOSITION / delegation: the whole effect is
# ONE entailed deed, `do assign-llm-slot` on the caller's own being, carrying { slot, connectionId }.
# That seed op is itself WORD-SOLE (store/words/llm-connection), so this is words all the way down.
# The slot write (set-being at qualities.beingLlm.slots.<slot>) folds through the entailed path.
#
# WORD-SOLE (handler-less, Tabor's no-mirror law): this `.word` is the ONLY path. do.js's
# runOpWordToStore runs it through runWordToStore (runAsStore), so the entailed deed seals its OWN
# moment on the caller's reel. The op lays NO fact of its own, the entailed do:assign-llm-slot
# deed IS the record. No host read: a delegator reads nothing of the floor. connectionId
# omitted/null clears the slot.
#
# The bridge binds `caller` (the actor's beingId, the being the slot lands on) and the op
# `params` (slot, connectionId), spread top-level too.

When a being assigns a slot of its own:
  If no caller, refuse with "assign-slot requires an authenticated being." as unauthorized.
  do assign-llm-slot on the being $caller with { slot: $params.slot, connectionId: $params.connectionId } as assigned.
  Return assigned: $assigned.
